Dear Lennart,

Am Mon, Feb 21, 2022 at 12:44:32AM +0100 schrieb L.C. Karssen:
> Thanks for contacting me. I agree, let's remove ProbABEL from Debian,
> completely. The package is no longer actively maintained and I have
> neither had any support requests, nor public bug reports in the last
> year, maybe two.

Thanks a lot for your opinion.  For the moment I decided to exclude all
architectures with failing tests and ask ftpmaster to remove the other
architectures.  In addition I've added a warning to README.Debian about
the current status and that this package might be removed in the next
Debian release.  Hope that can be considered a sensible compromise.

Kind regards
    Andreas.

